SELECT
	cdd_measure_customer,
	checked_by,
	checked_date,
	customer_nric,
	customer_type,
	id,
	id_cddmeasures,
	measure1,
	measure10,
	measure11,
	measure12,
	measure13,
	measure2,
	measure3,
	measure4,
	measure5,
	measure6,
	measure7,
	measure8,
	measure9,
	measure_result,
	remark1,
	remark10,
	remark11,
	remark12,
	remark13,
	remark2,
	remark3,
	remark4,
	remark5,
	remark6,
	remark7,
	remark8,
	remark9,
	representing
FROM cdd_measures
name: cdd_measures-admin

label.English: Do you suspect that the client is not the BO* of this property transaction?
Does the property transaction have no apparent economic* or lawful purpose*?
Is the client or BO from higher risk countries*?

If the property transaction is of higher risk, have you conducted enhanced CDD measures by asking the following information from the client or BO, i.e. occupation, source of funds/wealth and purpose of the transaction.
Have you sought approval from your estate agent to continue with the property transaction?
If the client is not the BO, are you able to verify the identify of the BO?
In the screening of the client or BO against the UN Sanction Lists, is there any full name match or partial name match where the nationality and age range matched*?
Is the client or BO known to be involved in FT, or proliferation financing?
Have you screened the client or BO against the list of entities identified in the Panama Papers?
In the screening of the client or BO against the Panama Papers, is there any name match?
Do you have reasons to believe that the client or BO is a PEP*?
If the client or BO is a PEP, is the client or BO a foreign PEP, a family member* or close associate* of a foreign PEP?
Is the property transaction complex*, or unusually large*?

Family member means a parent, step-parent, child, step-child, adopted child, spouse, sibling, step-sibling and adopted sibling of the PEP. Close associate means an individual who is closely connected to a PEP, either socially or professionally.

{BEGIN measure8_label} If your answer is Yes to the above question, ask for the source of the PEPs funds/wealth and to seek approval from your estate agent whether to continue with the property transaction.
